    <div>
        <h1 class='header'>Media Challenge</h1>
        <p class='body'>For 100 days I will be changing the way I interact with the internet, avoiding many of the platforms/features that prioritze maximizing engagement. Instead, I will adopt a more focused and intentional approach. I am curious what effects (if any) this approach will have on my attitudes, emotions, attention span, anxiety levels, etc.</p>
    </div>

    <h2 style='color: white;'>What I will avoid in particular:</h2>
    <ol class='body'>
        <li>Passive usage of social platforms.</li>
        <li>Infinite scroll.</li>
        <li>Recommendation algorithms.</li>
        <li>Short-form content.</li>
    </ol>

    <p class='body'>"No passive usage" for me means no visiting a site out of boredom. I also included politically-centered content because the news outlets are incentivized to to maximize engagement just like social media platforms and thus often use the same, emotionally manipulative tactics.</p>

    <p class='body'>These restrictions make it easy to disqualify many platforms from usage. I will have to make some clarifying decisions for others.</p>

            <table class='table'>
                <!-- headers -->
                <tr>
                    <td>Permitted</td>
                    <td>Not Permitted</td>
                </tr>

                <!-- data -->
                <tr>
                    <td>YouTube*</td>
                    <td>News Outlets (Fox, CNN, WSJ, etc.)</td>
                </tr>
